An **atom** is the smallest particle found in an element that can take part in a chemical reaction. Particles that are smaller than the atom are called **subatomic particles**. The three main **subatomic particles** that form an atom are **protons**, **neutrons**, and **electrons**. Protons and neutrons are collectively known as **nucleons**. The centre of the atom is called the **nucleus**.

